    <briefdescription>
<para>ECHO request/response callback structure. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This structure is used for tracking the ECHO request/response signaling packets of L2CAP BR. It is registered with the help of the <ref refid="group__bt__l2cap__br_1ga62c0115185f5026c1a842848dc5336ce" kindref="member">bt_l2cap_br_echo_cb_register()</ref> API. It&apos;s permissible to register multiple instances of this <ref refid="structbt__l2cap__br__echo__cb" kindref="compound">bt_l2cap_br_echo_cb</ref> type, in case different modules of an application are interested in tracking the ECHO request/response signaling packets. If a callback is not of interest for an instance, it may be set to NULL and will as a consequence not be used for that instance. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
